rComments: The course is very challenging!  You must read before coming to class or you'll easily get lost.  Ask her questions--she is very helpful.  In fact, she dedicates a lot of her lec time to answering students' questions.  She WANTS you to get the material.  So take advantage of a prof like her.  Not many are that eager to help students.  Fair prof.
Her lecture are extremely long, and boring, but its possible to get a good mark.

Spends two hours on lectures that she could get through in about half an hour, but I do respect her concern with making sure everyone gets the material. She's very organized, provides you with the most detailed lecture notes I have ever seen, assignments are easy and tests are fair. Highly recommended for that extra half credit.
It's very hard to sit through her lectures because she just drones on and on over the most trivial points.
